{"_attachments":{},"_id":"babel-plugin-transform-for-of-as-array","_rev":"293872-61f1c8c70053da98910fe237","author":{"name":"Justin Ridgewell","email":"justin+github@ridgewell.name"},"description":"Transform all for-of loops into the equivalent array for loop","dist-tags":{"latest":"1.1.1"},"license":"MIT","maintainers":[{"name":"jridgewell","email":"justin+npm@ridgewell.name"}],"name":"babel-plugin-transform-for-of-as-array","readme":"# babel-plugin-transform-for-of-as-array\n\nTransform all for-of loops into the equivalent array for loop\n\n## Example\n\n**In**\n\n```js\nconst array = [1, 2, 3];\nfor (const elm of array) {\n  console.log(elm);\n}\n\nlet item;\nfor ({ item } of array.map(item => ({ item }))) {\n  console.log(item);\n}\n```\n\n**Out**\n\n```js\nconst array = [1, 2, 3];\n\nfor (let _i = 0, _length = array.length; _i < _length; _i++) {\n  const elm = array[_i];\n  console.log(elm);\n}\n\nlet item;\nfor (let _i2 = 0, _array$map = array.map(item => ({ item })), _length2 = _array$map.length; _i2 < _length2; _i2++) {\n  ({ item } = _array$map[_i2]);\n\n  console.log(item);\n}\n```\n\n\n## `loose` transformation\n\nIn addition to the normal transform, we also support a null-ish checking `loose` transform. Passing `{ loose: true }` option into the plugin enables it:\n\n**In**\n\n```js\nconst array = null;\nfor (const elm of array) {\n  console.log(elm);\n}\n\nlet item;\nfor ({ item } of array.map(item => ({ item }))) {\n  console.log(item);\n}\n```\n\n**Out**\n\n```js\nconst array = null;\n\nfor (let _i = 0, _length = array == null ? 0 : array.length; _i < _length; _i++) {\n  const elm = array[_i];\n  console.log(elm);\n}\n\nlet item;\nfor (let _i2 = 0, _array$map = array.map(item => ({ item })), _length2 = _array$map == null ? 0 : _array$map.length; _i2 < _length2; _i2++) {\n  ({ item } = _array$map[_i2]);\n\n  console.log(item);\n}\n```\n\n\n## Installation\n\n```sh\n$ npm install babel-plugin-transform-for-of-as-array\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n### Via `.babelrc` (Recommended)\n\n**.babelrc**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"plugins\": [\"transform-for-of-as-array\"]\n}\n```\n\n### Via CLI\n\n```sh\n$ babel --plugins transform-for-of-as-array script.js\n```\n\n### Via Node API\n\n```javascript\nrequire(\"babel-core\").transform(\"code\", {\n  plugins: [\"transform-for-of-as-array\"]\n});\n```\n","time":{"created":"2022-01-26T22:18:47.802Z","modified":"2022-01-26T22:18:47.802Z","1.1.1":"2018-02-08T06:08:59.860Z","1.1.0":"2018-02-01T06:55:13.150Z","1.0.4":"2017-10-15T23:45:41.244Z","1.0.3":"2017-04-30T17:09:03.417Z","1.0.2":"2017-04-30T04:14:59.206Z","1.0.1":"2017-04-30T01:57:37.002Z","1.0.0":"2017-04-29T22:22:00.447Z"},"versions":{"1.1.1":{"name":"babel-plugin-transform-for-of-as-array","version":"1.1.1","description":"Transform all for-of loops into the equivalent array for loop","repository":{"type":"git","url":"git+https://github.com/jridgewell/babel-plugin-transform-for-of-as-array.git"},"author":{"name":"Justin Ridgewell","email":"justin+github@ridgewell.name"},"main":"lib/index.js","license":"MIT","devDependencies":{"babel-cli":"^7.0.0-beta.2","babel-plugin-transform-es2015-modules-amd":"^7.0.0-beta.2","babel-plugin-transform-es2015-modules-commonjs":"^7.0.0-beta.2","babel-preset-env":"^2.0.0-beta.2","mocha":"^2.2.5"},"scripts":{"clean":"rm -rf lib","build":"babel src -d lib","test":"mocha --compilers js:babel-register","test:watch":"npm run test -- --watch","prepublish":"npm run clean && npm run build"},"keywords":["for","of","loop","array","babel-plugin"],"gitHead":"92f0a579420ce091a574120ed404ef5dc75ccfed","bugs":{"url":"https://github.com/jridgewell/babel-plugin-transform-for-of-as-array/issues"},"homepage":"https://github.com/jridgewell/babel-plugin-transform-for-of-as-array#readme","_id":"babel-plugin-transform-for-of-as-array@1.1.1","_npmVersion":"5.5.1","_nodeVersion":"9.1.0","_npmUser":{"name":"jridgewell","email":"justin+npm@ridgewell.name"},"dist":{"shasum":"f18fcbcbfa2b8caed1445c3153893d37439a6537","size":5048,"noattac